{ {'A TYPICAL DAY'(CONT.)}
tomorrow I could be at the school in conference with the Head Teacher, in my capacity as Chairman of the Governors, over some aspect of school life.
In between these activities there is my garden to cultivate. The necessary decorating tasks in the bungalow have also to be fitted in. In addition I am involved with our local Methodist Church where help in various aspects of the church has to be given from time to time. Holidays abroad and visits to relations in Suffolk and Wiltshire have also to be organised in between times. As the year progresses the garden continues to occupy my time.
